# ArcGIS Developer SDKs & APIs - Skill de Conocimiento Completo

## Descripción
Conocimiento completo de todos los SDKs, APIs y herramientas de desarrollo de ArcGIS para construir aplicaciones de mapeo y análisis espacial.

---

## 1. ArcGIS Maps SDK for JavaScript (v5.0+)

### Descripción
SDK principal para construir aplicaciones web interactivas con mapas 2D/3D en el navegador.

### Arquitectura v5.0 (Transición Widgets → Components):
- **Components** (`@arcgis/map-components`): Nuevo estándar basado en Web Components
- **Widgets**: DEPRECADOS desde v5.0, se eliminarán en v6.0 (Q1 2027)
- Los componentes tienen funcionalidad equivalente a los widgets del core API
- El core API sigue accesible a través de componentes

### Clases Principales:

```javascript
// Map - Contenedor de capas
import Map from "@arcgis/core/Map";
const map = new Map({
  basemap: "arcgis/topographic"
});

// MapView - Vista 2D
import MapView from "@arcgis/core/views/MapView";
const view = new MapView({
  map: map,
  container: "viewDiv",
  center: [-118.805, 34.027],
  zoom: 13
});

// SceneView - Vista 3D
import SceneView from "@arcgis/core/views/SceneView";
const scene = new SceneView({
  map: map,
  container: "viewDiv"
});
```

### Tipos de Capas Disponibles:
| Capa | Descripción |
|------|-------------|
| FeatureLayer | Datos vectoriales con atributos, editable |
| GraphicsLayer | Gráficos temporales/dinámicos |
| VectorTileLayer | Tiles vectoriales con estilos |
| TileLayer | Tiles raster pre-renderizados |
| MapImageLayer | Imágenes dinámicas del servidor |
| ImageryLayer | Datos raster/imagery |
| ImageryTileLayer | Tiles de imágenes |
| GeoJSONLayer | Datos GeoJSON |
| CSVLayer | Datos CSV con coordenadas |
| SceneLayer | Datos 3D (scene services) |
| BuildingSceneLayer | Modelos BIM 3D |
| IntegratedMeshLayer | Mallas 3D integradas |
| PointCloudLayer | Nubes de puntos 3D |
| StreamLayer | Datos en tiempo real |
| RouteLayer | Rutas y direcciones |
| ParquetLayer | Archivos Apache Parquet |
| KMLLayer | Datos KML/KMZ |
| WMSLayer, WMTSLayer, OGCFeatureLayer | Estándares OGC |

### Componentes/Widgets Principales:
- **Navegación**: Home, Zoom, Compass, NavigationToggle, Locate, Track
- **Información**: Popup, Feature, Features, Legend, Attribution
- **Búsqueda**: Search, BasemapGallery, BasemapToggle, LayerList, BasemapLayerList
- **Edición**: Editor, FeatureForm, FeatureTemplates, Sketch
- **Medición**: DistanceMeasurement2D, AreaMeasurement2D, DirectLineMeasurement3D, AreaMeasurement3D, ElevationProfile
- **Análisis 3D**: Daylight, ShadowCast, Slice, LineOfSight, BuildingExplorer
- **Datos**: FeatureTable, Bookmarks, TimeSlider, Print, CoordinateConversion
- **Routing**: Directions
- **AI (beta)**: Assistant component (chat con lenguaje natural para web maps)

### Instalación:
```bash
npm install @arcgis/core @arcgis/map-components
```

### Referencia API: https://developers.arcgis.com/javascript/latest/api-reference/

---

## 2. ArcGIS API for Python

### Descripción
API completa para scripting, automatización, análisis de datos y ciencia de datos geoespacial.

### Módulos Principales:

#### `arcgis.gis` - Modelo de Información GIS
```python
from arcgis.gis import GIS

# Conexión a ArcGIS Online
gis = GIS("https://www.arcgis.com", "username", "password")
# Conexión con API key
gis = GIS(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")
# Conexión a Enterprise
gis = GIS("https://portal.enterprise.com/portal", "username", "password")

# Buscar contenido
items = gis.content.search("population", item_type="Feature Layer")
# Gestionar usuarios
users = gis.users.search("*")
# Gestionar grupos
groups = gis.groups.search("transportation")
```

#### `arcgis.features` - Features y Feature Layers
```python
from arcgis.features import FeatureLayer, FeatureLayerCollection

# Acceder a feature layer
fl = FeatureLayer("https://services.arcgis.com/.../FeatureServer/0")
# Consultar features
features = fl.query(where="POPULATION > 100000")
# Spatially Enabled DataFrame (SeDF)
sdf = fl.query().sdf
# Editar features
fl.edit_features(adds=[feature1], updates=[feature2], deletes="1,2,3")
```

#### `arcgis.mapping` - Mapas y Escenas Web
```python
from arcgis.mapping import WebMap, WebScene

# Crear web map
wm = WebMap()
wm.add_layer(feature_layer)
wm.save(item_properties={"title": "Mi Mapa"})

# Abrir web map existente
wm = WebMap(gis.content.get("item_id"))
```

#### `arcgis.geocoding` - Geocodificación
```python
from arcgis.geocoding import geocode, reverse_geocode, batch_geocode

# Geocodificación simple
results = geocode("380 New York St, Redlands, CA")
# Geocodificación inversa
address = reverse_geocode([long, lat])
# Batch geocoding
addresses = ["Address 1", "Address 2", "Address 3"]
results = batch_geocode(addresses)
```

#### `arcgis.network` - Análisis de Redes
```python
from arcgis.network import RouteLayer
# Routing, service areas, closest facility, OD matrix
```

#### `arcgis.geoenrichment` - Enriquecimiento de Datos
```python
from arcgis.geoenrichment import enrich, Country
# Obtener datos demográficos para ubicaciones
enriched = enrich(study_areas=[{"geometry": point}])
```

#### `arcgis.raster` - Datos Raster e Imágenes
```python
from arcgis.raster import ImageryLayer
# Funciones de análisis raster, NDVI, clasificación, etc.
```

#### Otros Módulos Importantes:
- `arcgis.geometry` - Operaciones geométricas (buffer, intersect, union, etc.)
- `arcgis.geoprocessing` - Ejecutar herramientas de geoprocessing
- `arcgis.realtime` - Datos en tiempo real
- `arcgis.learn` - Machine learning y deep learning geoespacial
- `arcgis.apps` - Gestión de aplicaciones
- `arcgis.env` - Variables de entorno
- `arcgis.auth` - Autenticación

### Instalación:
```bash
conda install -c esri arcgis
# o
pip install arcgis
```

### Referencia API: https://developers.arcgis.com/python/latest/api-reference/

---

## 3. ArcGIS REST APIs

### Servicios de Localización (Location-Based Services):

#### Basemap Styles Service
```
GET https://basemapstyles-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/styles/v2/styles/{style}
Estilos: arcgis/streets, arcgis/navigation, arcgis/topographic, arcgis/outdoor,
         arcgis/light-gray, arcgis/dark-gray, arcgis/imagery, arcgis/oceans
```

#### Geocoding Service
```
# Geocode (find address candidates)
GET https://geocode-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/GeocodeServer/findAddressCandidates
Params: address, singleLine, category, location, outFields, maxLocations, f=json

# Reverse geocode
GET https://geocode-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/GeocodeServer/reverseGeocode
Params: location={x},{y}, outSR, f=json

# Suggest
GET https://geocode-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/GeocodeServer/suggest
Params: text, location, category, f=json

# Batch geocode
POST https://geocode-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/GeocodeServer/geocodeAddresses
Params: addresses (JSON array), f=json
```

#### Routing Service
```
# Rutas simples
GET https://route-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/Route/NAServer/Route_World/solve
Params: stops, barriers, returnDirections, directionsLanguage, f=json

# Service Areas (isócronas)
POST https://route-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/ServiceAreas/NAServer/ServiceArea_World/solveServiceArea
Params: facilities, defaultBreaks, travelDirection, f=json

# Closest Facility
POST .../ClosestFacility_World/solveClosestFacility
# OD Cost Matrix
POST .../ODCostMatrix_World/solveODCostMatrix
# Vehicle Routing Problem
POST .../VehicleRoutingProblem_World/solve
```

#### GeoEnrichment Service
```
POST https://geoenrich.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/World/GeoEnrichmentServer/GeoEnrichment/enrich
Params: studyAreas, dataCollections, analysisVariables, f=json
Soporta: Ring buffers, drive time areas, walk time areas
+15,000 variables, +150 países
```

#### Elevation Service
```
GET https://elevation-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/elevation/get
Params: lon, lat, units (meters/feet), f=json
```

#### Places Service
```
# Near Point search
GET https://places-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/places-service/v1/places/near-point
Params: x, y, radius, categoryIds, searchText, f=json

# Place details
GET https://places-api.arcgis.com/arcgis/rest/services/places-service/v1/places/{placeId}
```

### Servicios Enterprise (ArcGIS Server REST API):

#### Feature Service
```
# Query features
GET {serviceUrl}/FeatureServer/{layerId}/query
Params: where, outFields, geometry, geometryType, spatialRel, returnGeometry, f=json

# Add features
POST {serviceUrl}/FeatureServer/{layerId}/addFeatures
Body: features=[{geometry:{...}, attributes:{...}}]

# Update features
POST {serviceUrl}/FeatureServer/{layerId}/updateFeatures
# Delete features
POST {serviceUrl}/FeatureServer/{layerId}/deleteFeatures
# Apply edits
POST {serviceUrl}/FeatureServer/{layerId}/applyEdits
```

#### Map Service
```
GET {serviceUrl}/MapServer
GET {serviceUrl}/MapServer/{layerId}/query
GET {serviceUrl}/MapServer/export?bbox=...&size=...&f=image
```

#### Geoprocessing Service
```
# Ejecutar tarea (sync)
POST {serviceUrl}/GPServer/{taskName}/execute
# Ejecutar tarea (async)
POST {serviceUrl}/GPServer/{taskName}/submitJob
GET {serviceUrl}/GPServer/{taskName}/jobs/{jobId}
GET {serviceUrl}/GPServer/{taskName}/jobs/{jobId}/results/{paramName}
```

#### Portal REST API
```
# Buscar items
GET https://www.arcgis.com/sharing/rest/search
Params: q, num, start, sortField, f=json

# Obtener item
GET https://www.arcgis.com/sharing/rest/content/items/{itemId}
# Datos del item
GET https://www.arcgis.com/sharing/rest/content/items/{itemId}/data
# Agregar item
POST https://www.arcgis.com/sharing/rest/content/users/{username}/addItem
```

### ArcGIS REST JS (Librería JavaScript):
```javascript
import { geocode } from "@esri/arcgis-rest-geocoding";
import { ApiKeyManager } from "@esri/arcgis-rest-request";

const auth = ApiKeyManager.fromKey("YOUR_API_KEY");
geocode({ address: "1600 Pennsylvania Ave", authentication: auth })
  .then(response => console.log(response.candidates));
```

**Instalación REST JS:**
```bash
npm install @esri/arcgis-rest-request @esri/arcgis-rest-geocoding @esri/arcgis-rest-routing
```

### Referencia REST APIs: https://developers.arcgis.com/rest/

